formula_58
where formula_59 is the correlation time of the noise term. It can also be shown that the autocorrelation function of the particle velocity formula_2 is given by
formula_61
where we have used the property that the variables formula_62 and formula_63 become uncorrelated for time separations formula_64. Besides, the value of formula_65 is set to be equal to formula_66 such that it obeys the equipartition theorem. If the system is initially at thermal equilibrium already with formula_67, then formula_68 for all formula_13, meaning that the system remains at equilibrium at all times.

The velocity formula_70 of the Brownian particle can be integrated to yield its trajectory formula_71. If it is initially located at the origin with probability 1, then the result is
