<text>The equivalent rectangular bandwidth or ERB is a measure used in psychoacoustics, which gives an approximation to the bandwidths of the filters in human hearing, using the unrealistic but convenient simplification of modeling the filters as rectangular band-pass filters, or band-stop filters, like in tailor-made notched music training (TMNMT).

== Approximations ==
For moderate sound levels and young listeners, suggest that the bandwidth of human auditory filters can be approximated by the polynomial equation:

